$ Registry: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Terminal Server

{ fDenyTSConnections #fDenyTSConnections

  The value of `fDenyTSConnections` deterermins if another computer can connect to *this* computer with → Windows/Remote-Desktop-Services.
  -
  If the value is `0`, such connections are allowed, if it is `1`, connections are disallowed.

  The following → Windows/PowerShell command line sets the value to `0` so that connections are allowed:
  gh|about-Windows-Registry|/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/SYSTEM/CurrentControlSet/Control/Terminal Server/allow-remote-connections.ps1||


}
